Roles are used to define permissions that allow users assigned to each role to access the services, dashboards and functions available on the Doxee Platform.

The **Roles **panel allows to view, add and manage roles defined on the Doxee Platform, associating users and refining access permissions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- [Creating a role](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#creating-a-role)

- [Viewing the details of a role](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#viewing-the-details-of-a-role)

> Tip

Here are some examples of typical user roles:

- **Deployer**: can deploy any resource on a specific tenant.

- **Editor**: can do everything on all resources in the DP3 Repository, both in the resource editor and in the Release &amp; Deploy panel.

- **Batch jobs manager**: can do everything in the Inputs, Jobs, and Outputs views of the Batch Jobs service's UI.

- **Batch jobs viewer**: can access the Batch Jobs service's UI, search and download data in the Inputs, Jobs, and Outputs views.

- **On-demand jobs manager**: can do everything in the Workflows and Jobs views of the On-Demand Jobs service's UI.

- **On-demand jobs viewer**: can access the On-Demand Jobs service's UI, search and download data in the Workflows and Jobs views.

### Creating a role
- Click **Add**. The **Create Role **form is displayed.

- Enter the required information in each section of the form, as described below:

[General information](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#general-information)

- [Services](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#services)

- [Permissions](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#permissions)

- [Users](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#users)

- [Attributes](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#attributes)

- [Tags](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#tags)

- Click **Save **to confirm.

#### General information
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Role name**

X

Name of the company (a combination of alphanumeric characters, spaces, and special characters)

**Environments**

Select the dashboards enabled for this role.

**Platforms**

Select the Platform installations enabled for this role.

**Accounts**

Select the accounts enabled for this role.

**Companies**

Select the companies enabled for this role.

**Dashboards**

Select the dashboards enabled for this role.

#### Services
![](data:image/png;base64,)

This section allows to select which services will be available to the users assigned to this role.

Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Services**

Select the services enabled for this role.

#### Permissions
![](data:image/png;base64,)

This section allows to select the permissions for each service that will be available to the user assigned to this role.

> Note

Access to the Home Page service is enabled by default.

#### Users
![](data:image/png;base64,)

This section allows to associate users with a role.

Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Username**

Select the users to associate with this role, searching by username.

> Note

Federated users are listed using their SSO login username (e.g. *user@doxee.com).*

> Note

A role may be assigned to multiple users. A user may have multiple roles.

> Important

Users that are not associated with any roles cannot access any data on the Doxee Platform.

#### Attributes
![](data:image/png;base64,)

This section allows to define attributes to map DP3 roles to existing DP2 roles, in order to avoid further logins for users accessing DP2 services from Doxee Platform 3.

Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Key**

Enter the name of the attribute key, using one of the following templates:

- *&lt;platform_instance&gt;-client *(specifying the name of the client)

- *&lt;platform_instance&gt;-group *(specifying the name of the external group to which the user should belong on DP2, in case the user should belong to multiple groups)

**Value**

Enter the value to use for the attribute.

> Important

In case of an attribute key expressed as *&lt;platform_instance&gt;-client*, if the user is not local on Doxee Platform 2 but logs in using an external identity provider, the **Value **field must be set to the same value indicated in the **Identity Provider &gt; Provider Name **field on DP2 for the identity provider this user is associated with.

> Note

It is possible to define multiple attributes: one *&lt;platform_instance&gt;-client *attribute and one or more *&lt;platform_instance&gt;-group *attributes.

#### Tags
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Tags**

Enter one or more tags (up to 10 tags, separated by a comma) to label the company. Tags may have a maximum length of 20 characters.

> Note

For more information on how to create accounts, companies and users, see:

- [Doxee Platform Settings - Accounts](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-accounts)

- [Doxee Platform Settings - Companies](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-companies)

- [Doxee Platform Settings - Users](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-users)

### Editing a role
- Click on the name of a role to view its details.

or:

Select the role that you want to modify and click **Edit**.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Edit the required information.

> Note

For more information on the available fields, see [Creating a role](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles#creating-a-role) above.

- Click **Update **to confirm.

> Tip

If you make any changes to the role details and then click on a different tab or the **Back **browser button, the system displays the following prompt, allowing you to save, discard, or cancel the changes.
